Question arises - Was killing the mentally ill woman the only solution?

rawContent:
On this #MentalHealthAwarenessWeek I'm not afraid to say that my #mentalhealth isn't great right now. My #depression symptoms are kicking my ass. Then comes the guilt for all of the things I "should" be doing, which is then followed by crippling #anxiety. I've been here a million times, and I know at some point, I'll be OK, but getting to that point is a constant struggle that leaves you feeling beaten, battered, and bruised. Keep talking about it, my friends.
#KeepTalkingMH #MentalHealthAwareness #bipolar

media.altText:
Tumblr user void-star:
Love bombing is not a euphemism for "too much affection too soon," or "high desire for contact."
"Love bombing" is a term originally used in the context of cults to describe a deliberate and coordinated recruitment method that involved feigning friendship and interest in a potential recruit, via flattery, flirtation, physical affection, and very directed positive attention to everything the recruit says in order to lure them into the cult. 
Since cults and abusive relationships operate in similar ways and use similar tactics, love bombing in an interpersonal relationship looks like manufacturing closeness in order to trap someone into a relationship in which the abuser has all the control.
And I know these days there's a million bullshit junky articles out there that make you think this is a symptom of cluster b personality disorders, but there is no way for you to be love bombing somebody without realizing it.

media.altText:
On a white background, with a black line border - which has a vine motif in each corner - black text reads:

'Hope is a 'tug of war'.
You lose if you let it go,
Hope,
An endless flame,
Only extinguished 
If you blow.

Hope,
A voice 
that says you can,
when you feel you can't,
That whispers,
'You'll be ok'
In moments 
When you aren't.

And so 
let hope be 
the tiniest of sparks,
That keeps you together,
When you're falling apart.'

@Nelsims411 

#helenswriting

rawContent:
I sense God's
presence at the
bottom of
the Mon River.
I feel lust for the

black stretching
from this
point to the

moment I'm forgotten.

I'm so tired.
Everything
goes wrong in
perpetuity.

Hope soaks
into scars

and drifts

into smashed drywall.

#poetry #vss365 #depression

Eine #Depression ist weit mehr als ein mentales Tief. Dass wir einmal durchhängen, erschöpft und ausgelaugt sind, ist völlig normal. Jeder von uns hat glücklicherweise eine schwanke Stimmung und ist insofern auch in der Lage, aus einem Loch wieder selbstständig herauszukommen. Und genau darin liegt der Unterschied zu einer psychischen Erkrankung, welche nämlich nicht mehr eigenständig bewältigbar ist und so immanent und beständig manifest verharrt, dass es an emotionaler Schwingungsfähigkeit fehlt.
